Definition:  FORMAT_NAME(name)

Description: Displays a player name in an 11 space field with justification
             to the left to make it easier to print in tables.

Arguments  : string name - the name of the player.

Returns    : string - the name of the player with spaces padded.

Example    : FORMAT_NAME("foobar") -> "foobar     "

See also   : CFORMAT_NAME
